outer_space_objects <- readr::read_csv('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rfordatascience/tidytuesday/master/data/2024/2024-04-23/outer_space_objects.csv')
## Rows: 1175 Columns: 4
## ── Column specification ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## Delimiter: ","
## chr (2): Entity, Code
## dbl (2): Year, num_objects
## 
## ℹ Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
## ℹ Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
library(ggplot2)

library(ggplot2)

# Filter the data for the past 20 years
recent_data <- subset(outer_space_objects, Year >= max(outer_space_objects$Year) - 19)

# Aggregating the data here to get the total number of objects shot by each country
country_totals <- aggregate(num_objects ~ Entity, data = recent_data, sum)

# this is yo select the top ten countries as its own variable
top_10_countries <- head(country_totals[order(country_totals$num_objects, decreasing = TRUE), ], 10)


ggplot(data = top_10_countries, aes(x = reorder(Entity, -num_objects), y = num_objects)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", fill = "navyblue") +
  labs(title = "Top 10 Countries by Total Objects Shot into Outer Space (Past 20 Years)",
       x = "Country",
       y = "Total Number of Objects") +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))

ggplot(data = outer_space_objects, aes(x = Year, color = Entity)) +
  geom_density() +
  labs(title = "Density of Objects Shot into Outer Space Over Time",
       x = "Year",
       y = "Density")

#scrapping this because it doesnt fit and there are too many coutries. The data revolving around countries will likely all have to be warped around for use due to how many there are
# next I want to try makign a graph to show how many are objects are shot into space per year. The stpry I am trying to portray is that people are shoting objects into space much more in recent years.

# Filtering the data again, this time for the past 50 years
recent_data <- subset(outer_space_objects, Year >= max(outer_space_objects$Year) - 49)

# Aggregating the data again to get the total number of objects shot per year
yearly_totals <- aggregate(num_objects ~ Year, data = recent_data, sum)

# Create the line plot
ggplot(data = yearly_totals, aes(x = Year, y = num_objects)) +
  geom_line(color = "grey") +
  labs(title = "Total Objects Shot into Outer Space (50 Yrs)",
       x = "Year",
       y = "Total Number of Objects")
